Proposal to make TraitDictionary a singleton or to remove it. And to make TraintContainer<T> instances also global singletons.

I.e. ```TraitContainer<T>.Singleton```

The advantage is that the trait container for a type can by looked up by relying on .net to resolve the generic type and accessing the singleton. There is no longer need for the lookup of the TraitContainer inside the TraitDictionary. For a 15 minute multi player game it results 20 million less function calls and hash table lookups. 

Disadvantage is that when a new World is created the TraitContainers may need to be emptied manually. The adding of traits becomes slower due to the need of reflection.  
 

