Also by removing the TraitDictionary member from World and calling TraitContainer<T>.Singleton.GetMultiple() directly saves the lookup of 2 levels of indirection x 20 million calls. I.e. in Actor.cs not Actor.World.TraitDictionary.TraitContainer.GetMultiple().

In at least the below places in the code the expensive ToArray method is called inbetween two Enumerable Select calls. They are not needed/overhead? You could have 2 Selects in a row or combine all in one Select?

Performance impact is minor, but the amount of these statements may grow as code is copied.

```bash
 find . -type f -name "*cs"  -exec  grep -H -i "ToArray().Sel" {} \; | grep -v electable
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Air/Aircraft.cs:                    speedModifiers = self.TraitsImplementing<ISpeedModifier>().ToArray().Select(sm => sm.GetSpeedModifier());
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Armament.cs:                        rangeModifiers = self.TraitsImplementing<IRangeModifier>().ToArray().Select(m => m.GetRangeModifier());
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Armament.cs:                        reloadModifiers = self.TraitsImplementing<IReloadModifier>().ToArray().Select(m => m.GetReloadModifier());
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Armament.cs:                        damageModifiers = self.TraitsImplementing<IFirepowerModifier>().ToArray().Select(m => m.GetFirepowerModifier());
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Armament.cs:                        inaccuracyModifiers = self.TraitsImplementing<IInaccuracyModifier>().ToArray().Select(m => m.GetInaccuracyModifier());
./OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Mobile.cs:                  speedModifiers = Exts.Lazy(() => self.TraitsImplementing<ISpeedModifier>().ToArray().Select(x => x.GetSpeedModifier()));

```

Also in Armament.cs the modifiers are stored are private enumerations and each time they are used inside the class the ToArray() method is called on the enumerations. Better to to store the enumerations are array to begin with.

In general arrays are faster than Enumerations, yet Enumeration.ToArray() is expensive.

